      • creationChemin

        public void creationChemin(ArrayList<Monument> listeMonument)
                    throws IOException,
                           org.json.JSONException
        This method set up the "chemin_a_prend" attribute. It's applying a mathematical algorithm (graph stuff) on the Monument List, and sorted them so the total path going through each monument is the shortest/fastest possible.
        Parameters:
        listeMonument - A list of Monument Object, no need to be sorted by any kind of parameters
        Throws:
        IOException
        org.json.JSONException

      • creationGraph

        public org.jgrapht.graph.SimpleWeightedGraph<Monument,org.jgrapht.graph.DefaultWeightedEdge> creationGraph(ArrayList<Monument> monuments)
                                                                                                    throws IOException,
                                                                                                           org.json.JSONException
        This method used the Matrix API to create a matrix of distances between each monument given as parameters, with those data, this method create a non oriented valuated graph of the Monuments. Each edge represents the distance between each Monuments.
        Parameters:
        monuments - A ArrayList of Monuments Object.
        Returns:
        A SimpleWeightGraph Object : a graph with ordered monuments on it.
        Throws:
        IOException
        org.json.JSONException

      • plusCoursCycle

        public ArrayList<Chemin> plusCoursCycle(org.jgrapht.graph.SimpleWeightedGraph<Monument,org.jgrapht.graph.DefaultWeightedEdge> g)
        Based on a SimpleWeightedGraph Object (obtained through "creationGraph" method). In this graph which isn't oriented but valuated, the method try to find an optimal cycle.
        Parameters:
        g - A SimpleWeightedGraph Object (see creationGraph method)
        Returns:
        An ArrayList of Chemin Objects
